The paper discusses the pitfalls and practical ways to deal with them in conducting software engineering surveys. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also touches upon the design of a questionnaire, which falls under the sub-category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of capturing a large-scale snapshot of the state of the practice, which could be categorized under cs.CY (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper emphasizes the need for improving the quality of research results, which could be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
